    "recap_headline": "University of Minnesota Athletics",
    "recap_text": "URBANA, ILL. \u2013\nThe University of Minnesota baseball team hit the road for their first Big Ten Conference matchup of the 2026 season against the University of Illinois tonight, falling in extra innings 2-1 at Illinois Field.\nJoe Sperry\ncame out of the bullpen for Minnesota and was credited with the loss, tossing three innings and striking out two.\nCole Selvig\nwas a bright spot for the Gophers, starting the ballgame and throwing 6.1 innings with three strikeouts.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nThe Gophers got on the scoreboard first in the ball game, tallying the first run\u00a0in the fourth inning on a leadoff solo home run over the right center field wall from\nEaston Richter\n.\nThe Illini tied the score back up in the fifth, driving in a run on a sacrifice bunt to the right side of the infield. The score remained tied 1-1 till the end of regulation, sending the game into extra innings.\nThe Illini were the first to score in extra innings, driving in a run in the bottom of the tenth on a bases loaded single to end the game.\nGAME NOTES\n\u00bb Minnesota's highest scoring inning was the fourth, when it pushed one run across.\n\u00bb Selvig put together 6.1 innings of one-run ball for Minnesota.\n\u00bb Minnesota pitchers faced 44 Illinois hitters in the game, allowing 12 ground balls and 11 fly balls while striking out five.\n\u00bb The Gophers drew five walks from Illinois pitching.\n\u00bb Richter led the Gophers at the plate, going 1 for 5 with a home run and an RBI."
